explanation: This problem can be solved using dynamic programming. We create a 2D array dp where dp[i][j] represents the number of ways to buy i pencils and j pens with total amount of money. If the total cost of pencils and pens exceeds the total amount of money, we only consider the pens. We fill up the dp array in a bottom-up manner and return the last element of the array.

